    @Override
    public void iterateNeighbors(
            Vertex<Long, Tuple2<Double, HashSet<Long>>> vertex,
            Iterable<Tuple2<Edge<Long, Double>, Vertex<Long, Tuple2<Double, HashSet<Long>>>>> neighbors,
            Collector<Tuple3<Long, Long, Double>> out) throws Exception {
        for(Tuple2<Edge<Long, Double>, Vertex<Long, Tuple2<Double, HashSet<Long>>>> neighbor : neighbors) {
            HashSet<Long> intersection = vertex.getValue().f1;
            intersection.retainAll(neighbor.f1.getValue().f1);
            for(long l : intersection) {
                System.out.println(neighbor.f1.getId()+" "+l);
                    out.collect(new Tuple3<Long, Long, Double>(neighbor.f1.getId(), l, vertex.getValue().f0));
                }
        }

    }

}
```

For some reason the output changes everytime I run it.... For some reason the operation of groupReduce and printing starts before this operation is completed. So I kept the getTriplets method which is working properly at least for the small datasets that I checked.
